narratives.question_text: Were the resources available to you - library, fabrication labs, classroom, software, desk space, etc. adequate for the fulfillment of the assigned work?  If not, please make suggestions.
comments: Yes but they were not well utilized by this course, even though they could have been for testing and fabrication. Also Josh Rowley needs to change his attitude and be more helpful to students. He calls himself an instructor so its about time he start acting like one instead always acting irritated and moody.
The resources have been excellent for the class.
yes.hopefully the fabrication shop will continue to be equally accommodating as we embark on the construction of the pavilion.
We shall see what the summer brings, but the up till this point the fabrication lab and its staff have been very available to us and adequate for the class to move forward.
The Haas Library is useless with their current lending policies.
